On Military Spouse Day, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation to honor military spouses for their selfless service, contributions, and sacrifices. He recognized their ability to balance the demands of military life and highlighted their support for their loved ones in the Armed Forces. The President acknowledged the unique challenges military spouses face in obtaining and retaining employment, such as occupational licensing requirements and lower wages. He mentioned legislation that changed residency requirements and increased reimbursement amounts for licensing costs to alleviate some of these obstacles. The administration is also working with various sectors to create job opportunities and economic empowerment for military spouses. President Trump called on Americans to show gratitude and honor military spouses through appropriate ceremonies and activities.